1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 5 MRSA ยง286-M, sub-ยง13 is enacted to read:
3 13. Electronic briefings to prospective enrollees. The division shall provide
4 electronic briefings regarding the program every 2 months to newly hired county or
5 municipal law enforcement officers or municipal firefighters who are eligible to enroll in
6 the program.
7 Sec. 2. Open enrollment of Retired County and Municipal Law
8 Enforcement Officers and Municipal Firefighters Health Insurance Program
9 for current employees. Notwithstanding the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 5, section
10 286-M, subsection 5, from October 1, 2025 to November 30, 2025, a county or municipal
11 law enforcement officer or a municipal firefighter who is employed in the position of a
12 county or municipal law enforcement officer or a municipal firefighter and who previously
13 elected not to enroll in the Retired County and Municipal Law Enforcement Officers and
14 Municipal Firefighters Health Insurance Program established in Title 5, section 286-M may
15 elect to enroll in the program.
16 For the purposes of this section, "county or municipal law enforcement officer" and
17 "municipal firefighter" have the same meanings as in Title 5, section 286-M, subsection 2,
18 paragraphs A and H, respectively.
19 SUMMARY
2200 This bill provides that a county or municipal law enforcement officer or a municipal
2211 firefighter who is employed in the position of a county or municipal law enforcement
2222 officer or a municipal firefighter and who previously elected not to enroll in the Retired
2233 County and Municipal Law Enforcement Officers and Municipal Firefighters Health
2244 Insurance Program may enroll from October 1, 2025 to November 30, 2025. The bill also
2255 requires the Department of Administrative and Financial Services, Bureau of Human
2266 Resources, Office of Employee Health and Wellness to provide electronic briefings
2277 regarding the program every 2 months to newly hired county or municipal law enforcement
2288 officers or municipal firefighters who are eligible to enroll in the program.
